rt with one of the conventional commit types. -->\r\n<!--- The conventional commit types for Semantic PR are: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, build, ci, chore, revert -->\r\n\r\n#### Description\r\n<!--- Describe your changes in detail -->\r\nThe installation script warns about `BIN_DIR` not being found in `$PATH` when the users pass a trailing forward slash.\r\n\r\nThis has been discussed in #1310, #1341, and #3486.\r\n\r\n#### Motivation and Context\r\n<!--- Why is this change required? What problem does it solve? -->\r\n<!--- If it fixes an open issue, please link to the issue here. -->\r\nCloses #3493\r\n\r\n#### Screenshots (if appropriate):\r\n\r\n#### How Has This Been Tested?\r\n<!--- Please describe in detail how you tested your changes. -->\r\n<!--- Include details of your testing environment, tests ran to see how -->\r\n<!--- your change affects other areas of the code, etc. -->\r\n- [x] I have tested using **MacOS**\r\n- [ ] I have tested using **Linux**\r\n- [x] I have tested using **Windows**\r\n\r\nAs discussed in #1310, #1341, and #3486, we see that all users passed a trailing slash for `bin-dir`;`/usr/bin/`, `/c/Users/slapbot/starship/` and `\"$HOME/.starship/bin/\"`, respectively.\r\n\r\nSince it is possible to have a trailing slash on a directory in `$PATH`, this prevents false-negatives when either or both directories contain a forward slash.\r\n\r\n#### Checklist:\r\n<!--- Go over all the following points, and put an `x` in all the boxes that apply. -->\r\n<!--- If you're unsure about any of these, don't hesitate to ask. We're here to help! -->\r\n- [ ] I have updated the documentation accordingly.\r\n- [ ] I have updated the tests accordingly.\r\n\r\nI couldn't find tests for this, but I'll be happy to add them if required.\r\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/starship/starship/issues/3723/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"http